data.enText: a small fruit that grows on a bush. There are several types of berry , some of which can be eaten.

data.chText: 鸟类靠坚果和浆果过冬。
data.enText: Birds feed on nuts and berries in the winter.

tr: any of numerous small and pulpy edible fruits
used as desserts or in making jams and jellies and preserves
a small fruit having any of various structures, e.g., simple (grape or blueberry) or aggregate (blackberry or raspberry)

example: We went berrying in the summer

value.def: Berries are small, round fruit that grow on a bush or a tree. Some berries are edible, for example blackberries and raspberries.
